						<summary>

						<p>Sētupati, Muttu-vayiravanātha Sētupati Kāttadēvar, Śaka 1642, Vikāri = A.D. 1720.</p>						

						<p>This is about the construction of a pavilion <hi rend="italic">(kūḍam)</hi> for the ablution ceremony in the tank called Sūryapuṭkaraṇi in front of the temple of Āḍāṉai-Nāyakar Aṉbirpiriyāda-Ammaṉ for the merit of Muttu-vayiravanātha Sētupati-kāttadēvar. The latter is given several high-sounding attributes.</p>						

						</summary>
